data.text:
About Southeast Edmonton Real Estate

From bungalows to one and two-storey traditional homes, both newer and older, there's plenty to start your search in Southeast Edmonton. Property for sale can include views of nearby ponds, golf course fairways, walking trails and more. At a higher price point, you can enjoy features like coffered ceilings, glass railing decks, walk-in closets, granite bath vanities, finished basements and more.

Townhouses can also be found amidst Southeast Edmonton real estate at affordable price points. Interiors offer stainless steel appliances, hardwood floors and double car garages. Vintage home options, at a lower price point, are available for those creative minds seeking a diamond in the rough that's just waiting to be polished up.

Southeast Edmonton Homes & Lifestyles

This area has many activities, resources, and recreational entertainment. Mill Woods Town Centre is a popular shopping destination with plenty of diverse restaurants, and each year the local community of recreational coordinators work together to put on the Southeast Edmonton Winter Fun Festival.

Outdoor activities amidst Southeast Edmonton homes for sale include the Mill Woods Golf Course, Jackie Parker Recreational Area, Pioneer Meadows Golf Course, and Wild Rose Park. Public transit serves the area well, with the commonly used #15 bus route that runs directly from Mill Woods Town Center to downtown every 30 minutes. There are also many well-reputed schools in the area including J. Percy Page High School, which is well known for its apprenticeship programs.
